ce:section.ce:para:
The constructed 3D analysis model was applied to the simultaneous detection of Hg2+ and Pb2+ in real water sample (sewage plant effluent). On the basis of testing the fluorescence changes after the addition of Hg2+ and Pb2+ to the actual water samples, the coordinates (I (436nm)/I0 (436nm), I (712nm)/I0 (712nm)) were substituted into the 2D x-y projection image of the 3D model (the coordinate diagram as shown in Fig. 10
                        ). The respective concentrations of Hg2+ and Pb2+ in the actual samples are obtained by finding the concentrations corresponding to the two-dimensional coordinates. From Table 1
                        , we knew that the concentrations of Hg2+ and Pb2+ measured by the model were close to the actual concentrations, indicating the feasibility of UiO-66-NH2(Eu)-CD(s) for simultaneous detection of Hg2+ and Pb2+.
